f=Product/price/custom/price-change-governance/SKILL.md · in=discipline changing live price packaging: impact analysis, grandfathering existing customers, routing rule sends any change touching Governance locked commitment (price guarantee, grandfathering promise) through board. Silent repricing trust incident; price change logged proposal. · p=price change highest-trust action product takes touches customer's wallet often promise made them. Governance makes changes deliberate: their impact analyzed, existing customers handled honestly, commitments never breached quietly. · wu=validated pricing experiment (pricing-experiment-discipline) ready broad., Packaging restructured existing customers., Any live price plan changing up, down, repackaged. · st:/ Protocol=IMPACT ANALYSIS (who's affected, revenue delta, churn risk, which segments; existing new customers separated) LOCKED-COMMITMENT CHECK (does touch Governance locked commitment price guarantee, grandfathering clause, contractual cap? yes board proposal, board's triple-pass; Governance dormant until docs exist, proposal queues, anneal-style) GRANDFATHERING (existing customers old prices handled explicitly: honored, migrated notice, transitioned never silently repriced; default leans customer-favorable) COMMUNICATION PLAN (changes announced notice, discovered invoice echo/comms message, price owns substance) PROPOSAL (the whole change logged proposal impact grandfathering comms approved before ships; silent change trust incident) SHIP (versioned, recorded; metric reads revenue churn outcome). · in=Never silent price change logged, approved proposal; change customers discover their invoice trust incident, full stop (the monetization analogue metric's no-silent-definition rule). Locked commitments gate board change touching price guarantee grandfathering promise routes board (Governance); until Governance's docs exist proposal queues rather proceeding (most-restrictive default). Grandfather deliberately, customer-favorable default existing customers honored, migrated clear notice, transitioned stated terms; silently repricing someone who signed under old price cardinal sin. Impact separates existing new revenue/churn math different each; change that's great new customers punishing loyal ones flagged, averaged. Communication part change notice, clarity, honesty about why; price owns substance, echo/comms delivery; change ships without comms plan. · of=Price-change proposal: impact (existing new, revenue churn risk) locked-commitment check board scope) grandfathering plan comms plan approval ship (versioned) metric outcome read. · pr=Never silent change logged, approved proposal., Locked commitments gate board; queue Governance dormant., Grandfather customer-favorable default never silently reprice loyalty., Communication part change, afterthought. · f=Governance built (no locked-commitments doc)? Assume commitments exist proposal touching existing-customer prices queues board review defaults grandfathering, rather proceeding assumption there's promise (most-restrictive, Fleet Charter default). · b:with Other Skills=pricing-experiment-discipline supplies validated change; pricing-research/packaging-tiers supply new structure; metric reads revenue+churn outcome., board/precedent (Governance): locked-commitment changes gate board; precedent archives proposal verdict (Fleet Charter Rail pattern, pricing edition)., echo/comms (Executive Office): customer message; price owns substance. felix/Finance (future): margin impact co-cited.